# 📖 Book Finder

A modern, user-friendly web application that helps users discover and explore books using the Open Library API. Built with React and designed specifically for book lovers like Alex, a college student who needs an efficient way to search and organize books.

![Book Finder App](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-18.0+-blue.svg)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green.svg)

## 🌟 Features

### Core Functionality
- **Multiple Search Methods**
  - 📚 Search by Book Title
  - ✍️ Search by Author Name
  - 🎭 Search by Subject/Genre

- **Rich Book Information Display**
  - High-quality book cover images
  - Author names and publication details
  - Publisher information and ISBN
  - Subject tags and categories
  - First publication year

- **Favorites System**
  - ❤️ Save favorite books with one click
  - View all saved favorites in a dedicated section
  - Persistent storage using localStorage
  - Remove books from favorites easily

- **User-Friendly Interface**
  - Clean, modern design with gradient backgrounds
  - Intuitive search controls with radio button selection
  - Responsive grid layout for book results
  - Visual feedback with hover effects and animations
  - Loading indicators and error messages

### Technical Features
- Real-time search with Open Library API
- Responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- Error handling and fallback UI
- Optimized image loading with placeholders
- Persistent data storage
- Fast performance with React state management

