## 🎯 How to Use

### Searching for Books

1. **Select Search Type**
   - Click one of the radio buttons: Title, Author, or Subject
   
2. **Enter Search Query**
   - Type your search term in the input field
   - Examples:
     - Title: "Harry Potter", "1984", "The Great Gatsby"
     - Author: "J.K. Rowling", "George Orwell", "Jane Austen"
     - Subject: "Science Fiction", "Mystery", "Romance"

3. **Click Search Button**
   - Results will appear in a grid layout below
   - Each book card shows cover, title, author, and more details

### Managing Favorites

1. **Add to Favorites**
   - Click the white heart (🤍) icon on any book card
   - The heart turns red (❤️) to show it's favorited

2. **View Favorites**
   - Click the "My Favorites" button at the top
   - See all your saved books in one place

3. **Remove from Favorites**
   - Click the red heart (❤️) icon again to remove
   - Changes are saved automatically

## 🌐 API Reference

This project uses the **Open Library Search API** (no authentication required)

### Endpoints Used:

**Search by Title:**
```
https://openlibrary.org/search.json?title={bookTitle}&limit=20
```

**Search by Author:**
```
https://openlibrary.org/search.json?author={authorName}&limit=20
```

**Search by Subject:**
```
https://openlibrary.org/search.json?subject={subject}&limit=20
```

**Book Cover Images:**
```
https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/{cover_id}-M.jpg
```

## 🔧 Available Scripts

### `npm start`
Runs the app in development mode.
Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in your browser.

### `npm test`
Launches the test runner in interactive watch mode.

### `npm run build`
Builds the app for production to the `build` folder.
Optimizes the build for best performance.

### `npm run eject`
**Note: this is a one-way operation. Once you eject, you can't go back!**

## 🚀 Deployment

### Deploy to Netlify

1. Build your project:
```bash
npm run build
```

2. Drag and drop the `build` folder to [Netlify](https://www.netlify.com/)

### Deploy to Vercel

1. Install Vercel CLI:
```bash
npm install -g vercel
```

2. Deploy:
```bash
vercel
```

### Deploy to GitHub Pages

1. Install gh-pages:
```bash
npm install gh-pages --save-dev
```

2. Add to package.json:
```json
"homepage": "https://yourusername.github.io/book-finder",
"scripts": {
  "predeploy": "npm run build",
  "deploy": "gh-pages -d build"
}
```

3. Deploy:
```bash
npm run deploy
```

## 🎨 Customization

### Changing Colors

Edit `src/App.css` to modify the color scheme:

```css
/* Primary gradient */
background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);

/* Button colors */
background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
```

### Modifying Search Results Limit

In `src/App.js`, change the limit parameter:

```javascript
let url = `https://openlibrary.org/search.json?title=${encodeURIComponent(searchQuery)}&limit=20`;
// Change 20 to your desired number
```

## 🐛 Troubleshooting

### Port 3000 Already in Use

**Windows:**
```bash
netstat -ano | findstr :3000
taskkill /PID <process_id> /F
```

**Mac/Linux:**
```bash
lsof -ti:3000 | xargs kill -9
```

### Module Not Found Error

```bash
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
```

### Build Fails

Clear cache and rebuild:
```bash
npm cache clean --force
npm install
npm run build
```

